content:
To modify the prompt using LaTeX code and include a requirement for a Venn diagram, you can format it as follows:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{tikz}
\begin{document}

\textbf{Prompt:}

Categorize the following description as \textit{ephemeral} or \textit{enduring}:

\begin{quote}
Nostalgia is the bittersweet longing for a past time or place that can never be revisited or relived.
\end{quote}

Provide two examples of each category. Additionally, include a Venn diagram to visually represent the relationship between the two categories.

\vspace{1cm}

\textbf{Examples:}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textit{Ephemeral:}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Example 1
        \item Example 2
    \end{itemize}
    \item \textit{Enduring:}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Example 1
        \item Example 2
    \end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

\vspace{1cm}

\textbf{Venn Diagram:}

\begin{center}
\begin{tikzpicture}
    \begin{scope}[blend group = soft light]
        \fill[red!30!white] ( 90:1.5) circle (2);
        \fill[green!30!white] (210:1.5) circle (2);
        \fill[blue!30!white] (330:1.5) circle (2);
    \end{scope}
    \node at ( 90:2.8)    {Ephemeral};
    \node at ( 210:2.8)   {Enduring};
    \node at ( 330:2.8)   {Shared Aspects};
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{center}

\end{document}
```

This LaTeX document will format the prompt, the request for examples, and include a simple Venn diagram using the `tikz` package to visually represent the relationship between the categories 'ephemeral' and 'enduring'. You can customize the Venn diagram further by adding specific elements or labels as needed.
